# Fractary Codex

This project uses the `fractary-codex` CLI and skills for knowledge management, document fetching, caching, and project-to-codex synchronization.

## Skills

Skills are in `plugins/codex/skills/*/SKILL.md`. Read the relevant skill for detailed guidance.

Available skills:
- **fractary-codex-config** — Initialize, update, or validate codex configuration
- **fractary-codex-sync** — Sync project with codex repository
- **fractary-codex-cli-helper** — Shared CLI invocation utility
- **fractary-codex-repo-discoverer** — Discover organization repositories for sync
- **fractary-codex-memory-audit** — Audit memory entries for validity
- **fractary-codex-memory-create** — Create structured memory entries

## CLI

Run `fractary-codex --help` for full usage. Key commands:
- `fractary-codex fetch <uri>` — Fetch a document by codex:// URI
- `fractary-codex cache list|clear|stats|health` — Manage document cache
- `fractary-codex sync [--to-codex|--from-codex] [--work-id <id>]` — Sync with codex repository
- `fractary-codex config-init|config-update|config-validate` — Manage configuration

## Configuration

Configuration lives at `.fractary/config.yaml`. Validate with `fractary-codex config-validate`.
